WEBVTT

00:01.020 --> 00:03.040
NARRATOR: <i>Previously on</i>
The Handmaid's Tale...

00:03.040 --> 00:04.320
[AUNT LYDIA BLOWS WHISTLE]

00:04.320 --> 00:05.640
[WHIMPERING]
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

00:05.640 --> 00:07.430
AUNT LYDIA: Today we purify

00:07.430 --> 00:09.590
that most grievous of sins...

00:09.590 --> 00:11.790
the endangerment of a child.

00:11.790 --> 00:12.930
I try to think

00:12.930 --> 00:14.970
of the good I can do.

00:14.970 --> 00:18.430
If I can help
just one... person,

00:18.430 --> 00:19.430
that's enough.

00:19.430 --> 00:21.020
- You're with child?
- OFMATTHEW: Yes.

00:21.020 --> 00:23.060
May He make me truly worthy.

00:23.060 --> 00:25.180
- Again.
- Yes.

00:25.180 --> 00:26.560
Mrs. Mackenzie
asked you to stop!

00:26.560 --> 00:28.650
I just came from
my fourth hanging this week.

00:28.650 --> 00:31.030
Her school. In Brookline.
Go to the gate.

00:31.030 --> 00:32.740
Guardian Parker,
he's there today.

00:32.740 --> 00:34.530
OFJOSEPH: Would you like
to go for a walk?

00:34.530 --> 00:35.970
I... I really shouldn't.

00:35.970 --> 00:37.610
I'll make sure
nothing happens to you.

00:37.610 --> 00:38.620
Promise.

00:38.620 --> 00:40.240
[GIRLS SHOUTING PLAYFULLY]

00:40.240 --> 00:41.260
Hannah!

00:41.260 --> 00:42.320
ELEANOR: Show me the children!

00:42.320 --> 00:43.330
GUARDIAN: I can't have you like this...

00:43.330 --> 00:44.630
- Eleanor?
- ELEANOR: You left me.

00:44.630 --> 00:45.660
I'm so sorry.

00:45.660 --> 00:47.360
GUARDIAN: She won't stop
asking about the children!

00:47.360 --> 00:48.870
- Why is she talking...
- She's confused!

00:48.870 --> 00:50.130
Is Mrs. Lawrence okay?

00:50.130 --> 00:51.240
LAWRENCE: Do not presume

00:51.240 --> 00:54.970
to speak to me about my wife!

00:54.970 --> 00:55.980
ALMA: What happened?

00:55.980 --> 00:57.040
The Mackenzies are gone.

00:57.040 --> 00:58.340
- Gone where?
- ALMA: I don't know.

00:58.340 --> 00:59.590
Not even my Commander knows.

00:59.590 --> 01:00.890
OFMATTHEW: I saw you

01:00.890 --> 01:03.250
at Loaves and Fishes
talking to that Martha.

01:03.250 --> 01:04.260
- [MUFFLED SOBBING]
- [WHISTLE BLOWS]

01:06.440 --> 01:08.220
I saved you.

01:08.220 --> 01:10.120
Do you have any idea
what you did?

01:10.120 --> 01:11.390
You fucking bitch!

01:11.390 --> 01:13.190
Do you know what you did?

01:13.190 --> 01:14.780
[ECHOING]
Do you?

01:19.260 --> 01:20.300
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

01:20.300 --> 01:22.280
[WOMAN BREATHING HEAVILY]

01:24.230 --> 01:28.310
HANDMAIDS: [CHANTING] Breathe.

01:28.310 --> 01:29.310
[SAD PIANO MUSIC]

01:29.310 --> 01:30.370
AUNT LYDIA: Hold.

01:30.370 --> 01:33.240
HANDMAIDS: [CHANTING] Hold.

01:33.240 --> 01:35.610
- AUNT LYDIA: Exhale.
- HANDMAIDS: [CHANTING] Exhale.

01:35.610 --> 01:37.050
AUNT LYDIA: Exhale.

01:37.050 --> 01:38.210
[LABORED BREATHING CONTINUES]

01:38.210 --> 01:41.350
HANDMAIDS: [CHANTING] Breathe.

01:41.350 --> 01:43.250
Deeper breaths, Ofandy.

01:43.250 --> 01:45.520
You're doing beautifully.

01:45.520 --> 01:46.820
HANDMAIDS: [CHANTING] Exhale.

01:46.820 --> 01:48.750
JUNE: <i>Frances was Hannah's Martha.</i>

01:48.750 --> 01:50.460
<i>In the time before,</i>

01:50.460 --> 01:52.050
<i>Frances was a sales manager</i>

01:52.050 --> 01:53.730
<i>for a theatrical supply company.</i>

01:53.730 --> 01:54.860
HANDMAIDS:
Hold, hold.

01:54.860 --> 01:57.450
JUNE: <i>Frances tutored
kids after school.</i>

01:57.450 --> 01:58.670
<i>Frances was saving up</i>

01:58.670 --> 02:01.680
<i>for a trip to the Galapagos.</i>

02:01.680 --> 02:03.840
<i>Frances loved my daughter.</i>

02:03.840 --> 02:06.080
<i>Frances is dead.</i>

02:07.640 --> 02:10.020
<i>And Hannah is gone.</i>

02:10.020 --> 02:12.040
- OFMATTHEW: Blessed day.
- ALMA: Don't talk to her.

02:13.120 --> 02:15.040
JUNE: <i>Because of her.</i>

02:15.040 --> 02:16.050
[CURIOUS MUSIC]

02:16.050 --> 02:18.660
HANDMAIDS: [CHANTING] Breathe.

02:18.660 --> 02:21.820
Hold.

02:21.820 --> 02:25.960
Exhale.

02:25.960 --> 02:29.630
Breathe.

02:29.630 --> 02:33.340
Hold.

02:33.340 --> 02:36.670
Exhale.

02:36.670 --> 02:40.310
Breathe.

02:40.310 --> 02:43.750
Hold.

02:43.750 --> 02:47.320
Exhale.

02:47.320 --> 02:51.090
Breathe.

02:51.090 --> 02:54.390
Hold.

02:54.390 --> 02:58.260
Exhale.

02:58.260 --> 03:01.700
Breathe.

03:01.700 --> 03:05.130
Hold.

03:05.130 --> 03:06.370
You're being so mean.

03:06.370 --> 03:08.470
She got someone executed.

03:08.470 --> 03:10.040
She doesn't feel sorry about it.

03:10.040 --> 03:12.170
She should have kept
her fucking mouth shut.

03:13.680 --> 03:16.320
She was just doing what
Aunt Lydia told her to.

03:16.320 --> 03:17.480
Oh, I know.

03:17.480 --> 03:20.820
HANDMAIDS: [CHANTING] Exhale.

03:20.820 --> 03:24.320
Breathe.

03:24.320 --> 03:27.660
Hold.

03:27.660 --> 03:30.890
Exhale.

03:30.890 --> 03:34.330
Ofandy's contractions
have stopped.

03:34.330 --> 03:36.660
Until we can be of use,

03:36.660 --> 03:38.870
let us give her
some peace and quiet.

03:40.790 --> 03:43.240
[DISH CLATTERING]

03:43.240 --> 03:44.460
ALMA: Ofmatthew,

03:44.460 --> 03:46.030
shame on you.

03:46.030 --> 03:48.040
OFERIC: Butterfingers.

03:48.040 --> 03:50.010
AUNT LYDIA: Out you go, girls,

03:50.010 --> 03:52.030
back on the Birthmobile.

03:57.490 --> 04:00.060
Tell your friends to cool it.

04:00.060 --> 04:01.440
I'm sorry, Aunt Lydia.

04:01.440 --> 04:02.860
I don't know what
you're talking about.

04:05.930 --> 04:07.800
You want to take my tongue out?

04:07.800 --> 04:10.030
Burn my arm?
[CLICKS TONGUE]

04:10.030 --> 04:11.860
Better hope they don't
need me on TV again

04:11.860 --> 04:13.340
for Nichole.

04:15.050 --> 04:17.240
Get on the bus, dear.

04:17.240 --> 04:19.230
I don't think
we'll take you <i>all</i> home

04:19.230 --> 04:20.890
just yet.

