04:29.240 --> 04:32.720
AUNT LYDIA: That Martha was salvaged

04:32.720 --> 04:35.660
for plotting a heinous crime,

04:35.660 --> 04:39.060
the theft of a child.

04:39.060 --> 04:42.280
Who led her to conceive of such

04:42.280 --> 04:43.870
an evil act?

04:43.870 --> 04:48.040
HANDMAIDS: [CHANTING] She did.

04:48.040 --> 04:51.310
AUNT LYDIA: And whose fault
is it that the Martha died?

04:51.310 --> 04:54.640
HANDMAIDS: [CHANTING] Her fault.

04:57.750 --> 05:00.840
It's my fault, Aunt Lydia.

05:02.320 --> 05:05.050
AUNT LYDIA: Testifying is...

05:05.050 --> 05:08.260
where you unburden
yourself of sin,

05:08.260 --> 05:10.050
is that right?

05:10.050 --> 05:12.690
HANDMAIDS: Yes, Aunt Lydia.

05:14.060 --> 05:15.650
Perhaps you think of yourself

05:15.650 --> 05:17.770
as empty of sin.

05:17.770 --> 05:20.000
Mmm-mmm.

05:20.000 --> 05:22.260
No one is without sin,

05:22.260 --> 05:24.030
Aunt Lydia.

05:24.030 --> 05:25.880
AUNT LYDIA: That's exactly right.

05:25.880 --> 05:27.910
Yeah.

05:32.650 --> 05:35.030
In your selfishness,

05:35.030 --> 05:36.850
there is someone else

05:36.850 --> 05:39.590
you've forgotten you've wronged.

05:39.590 --> 05:42.250
Someone you've hurt deeply.

05:43.990 --> 05:45.860
That little girl Agnes,

05:45.860 --> 05:48.870
of course.

05:48.870 --> 05:50.200
That Martha loved

05:50.200 --> 05:53.540
and cared for her.

05:53.540 --> 05:55.840
Think of that little girl,

05:55.840 --> 05:57.660
without that warmth

05:57.660 --> 05:59.300
in her life.

06:02.460 --> 06:04.850
Whose fault is that?

06:07.250 --> 06:08.250
[DARK MUSIC]

06:08.250 --> 06:09.590
My fault.

06:09.590 --> 06:11.920
AUNT LYDIA: Mmm.

06:11.920 --> 06:13.340
Agnes's family was

06:13.340 --> 06:15.830
forced to relocate.

06:15.830 --> 06:18.690
She was ripped from her home,

06:18.690 --> 06:20.230
her friends, her school.

06:20.230 --> 06:22.170
Everything she knew.

06:22.170 --> 06:25.660
Her world is emptier

06:25.660 --> 06:29.770
and colder now than it ever was.

06:29.770 --> 06:33.440
Whose fault is that?

06:33.440 --> 06:34.870
[SOFTLY] It's my fault.

06:34.870 --> 06:36.350
AUNT LYDIA: Mmm.

06:36.350 --> 06:38.450
It is a wicked,

06:38.450 --> 06:39.780
<i>selfish</i> fool

06:39.780 --> 06:41.870
who chooses another wicked,

06:41.870 --> 06:44.260
selfish <i>fool</i>

06:44.260 --> 06:47.020
as her example.

06:47.020 --> 06:49.340
Especially when there are the...

06:49.340 --> 06:50.360
godly,

06:50.360 --> 06:52.250
obedient,

06:52.250 --> 06:53.440
and joyful

06:53.440 --> 06:55.090
among you.

07:02.000 --> 07:04.010
Yes, Ofjoseph.

07:05.740 --> 07:07.740
I have something
else to testify.

07:09.250 --> 07:11.280
AUNT LYDIA: What is that?

07:23.930 --> 07:27.130
Ofmatthew doesn't want her baby.

07:27.130 --> 07:28.300
[HANDMAIDS GASPING SOFTLY]

07:28.300 --> 07:30.320
Oh, shit.

07:34.820 --> 07:36.320
Is this true, Ofmatthew?

07:36.320 --> 07:38.360
No, Aunt Lydia.

07:48.020 --> 07:49.880
Testify.

07:52.460 --> 07:54.560
[STUTTERING]
I only felt that way

07:54.560 --> 07:55.670
for a second.

07:55.670 --> 07:58.050
Just a second.

08:00.870 --> 08:02.670
[SIGHS]

08:02.670 --> 08:04.970
Ofjoseph.

08:12.240 --> 08:14.880
Go on.
Go on.

08:25.320 --> 08:28.360
[STUTTERING]
Well, it was just a second.

08:29.870 --> 08:32.669
It just feels different.

08:32.669 --> 08:33.870
This one, I think it's a girl,

08:33.870 --> 08:35.240
and the others were boys,

08:35.240 --> 08:37.260
so I just, I got scared.

08:38.840 --> 08:41.270
Scared of what
her life would be.

08:41.270 --> 08:43.700
Only God knows that.

08:45.580 --> 08:48.620
She thinks she knows
better than God.

08:48.620 --> 08:51.060
[SCOFFS]
That's a sin.

08:51.060 --> 08:54.730
HANDMAIDS: [CHANTING] Sinner.

08:54.730 --> 08:56.240
AUNT LYDIA: And to refuse

08:56.240 --> 08:58.700
God's blessings of a child

08:58.700 --> 09:02.010
is among the gravest of sins.

09:02.010 --> 09:03.460
HANDMAIDS: [CHANTING] Sinner.

09:03.460 --> 09:06.850
[STUTTERING] No, no,
but I don't reject her.

09:06.850 --> 09:08.740
I want...
I want her!

09:08.740 --> 09:10.870
I swear I do!
I love her!

09:10.870 --> 09:11.980
I love her!

09:11.980 --> 09:13.280
HANDMAIDS: [CHANTING] Sinner.

09:13.280 --> 09:14.310
[STUTTERING] No, no!

09:14.310 --> 09:16.070
No! No, no! I want her!

09:16.070 --> 09:17.260
I swear I want her!

09:17.260 --> 09:20.870
I love her! I love her!

09:20.870 --> 09:22.170
AUNT LYDIA: Ofmatthew.

09:22.170 --> 09:24.160
Don't be a crybaby.

09:24.160 --> 09:36.450
HANDMAIDS: [CHANTING] Crybaby.

09:39.630 --> 09:41.650
[OFMATTHEW HOLDS BACK SOBS]

09:43.760 --> 09:45.880
AUNT LYDIA: There's
my good girl.

09:45.880 --> 09:46.900
[WHIMPERS]

09:46.900 --> 09:48.560
AUNT LYDIA: Oh!

09:51.450 --> 09:55.230
You feel better now, don't you?

09:55.230 --> 09:57.270
- Yes, Aunt Lydia.
- AUNT LYDIA: Hmm.

09:57.270 --> 09:59.310
[OFMATTHEW CONTINUES CRYING]

10:10.770 --> 10:13.780
[INDISTINCT RHYTHMIC CLATTERING]

10:16.040 --> 10:18.070
[WOMAN AND CHILD CHATTERING INDISTINCTLY]

10:18.070 --> 10:20.100
[SCHOOL BELL RINGING]

10:20.100 --> 10:21.260
RYAN: Am I alive?

10:21.260 --> 10:23.110
WOMAN: No.

10:23.110 --> 10:24.950
Was I a movie star?

10:24.950 --> 10:26.450
WOMAN: Mmm...

10:26.450 --> 10:28.290
Not exactly.

10:28.290 --> 10:29.850
I'd say no.

10:29.850 --> 10:32.260
RYAN: Are we studying
me right now in school?

10:32.260 --> 10:34.270
[CHUCKLES] Yes.

10:34.270 --> 10:35.690
Good question!

10:35.690 --> 10:36.970
Was I smart?

10:36.970 --> 10:38.660
LYDIA: Yes.

10:38.660 --> 10:41.440
JIM: You're still here.

10:41.440 --> 10:42.830
LYDIA: Keep thinking
of questions

10:42.830 --> 10:44.030
'cause I know you're gonna get

10:44.030 --> 10:46.040
a bright idea.

10:46.040 --> 10:47.510
[CARS HONKING OUTSIDE]

10:47.510 --> 10:49.850
I left her another message.

10:49.850 --> 10:51.440
I hope she's all right.

10:51.440 --> 10:52.670
SECURITY: Mr. Thorne,

10:52.670 --> 10:54.800
I'm sorry, it's 6:15.

10:56.080 --> 10:58.440
I think it's too cold
to wait outside.

10:58.440 --> 10:59.780
I'm gonna take him home.

10:59.780 --> 11:00.850
Are you sure?

11:00.850 --> 11:03.350
LYDIA: Sure.
It's no problem.

11:03.350 --> 11:06.780
"Don't forget to show
hospitality to strangers,

11:06.780 --> 11:10.560
for thereby some
have entertained the angels."

11:10.560 --> 11:12.780
Hebrews... 13.

11:12.780 --> 11:13.800
Yes!

11:13.800 --> 11:15.080
JIM: I've always
liked that chapter.

11:15.080 --> 11:16.120
Mmm.

11:17.750 --> 11:19.300
Are you hungry, honey?

11:19.300 --> 11:20.540
A little.

11:21.650 --> 11:23.670
- A bag of potato chips.
- JIM: Huh.

11:23.670 --> 11:26.710
That's what she
packed for his lunch.

11:28.210 --> 11:29.210
[DIALING]

11:29.210 --> 11:30.210
[PHONE RINGS]

11:30.210 --> 11:31.660
ANSWERING MACHINE: <i>Please leave a message.</i>

11:31.660 --> 11:33.450
[BEEPS]
Noelle.

11:33.450 --> 11:35.260
It's Lydia Clements again.

11:35.260 --> 11:37.130
I'm gonna take
Ryan home with me.

11:37.130 --> 11:38.890
Give me a buzz
when you get this,

11:38.890 --> 11:40.930
and I'll text you the address.

11:43.360 --> 11:44.730
I hope you like chili.

11:44.730 --> 11:46.650
The same chili you
made for in-service day?

11:46.650 --> 11:47.650
[LAUGHS] Yes.

11:47.650 --> 11:50.150
Oh! You're in for a treat.

11:50.150 --> 11:52.240
Miss Clements' chili is famous.

11:52.240 --> 11:53.510
[EVERYONE LAUGHS]

11:53.510 --> 11:56.020
NOELLE: Sorry.
I am so sorry!

11:56.020 --> 11:57.030
- Hey, buddy.
- RYAN: Mom!

11:57.030 --> 11:58.050
Hey.

11:58.050 --> 11:59.980
JIM: We were
starting to worry.

11:59.980 --> 12:01.410
I got held up at work.

12:01.410 --> 12:02.760
And I got here
as fast as I could.

12:02.760 --> 12:03.760
I'm so sorry.

12:03.760 --> 12:05.050
He's hungry.

12:05.050 --> 12:07.060
NOELLE: Um, we can stop
at a drive-through.

12:07.060 --> 12:08.480
On the way home, buddy, okay?

12:08.480 --> 12:10.980
We had McDonald's last night.

12:10.980 --> 12:12.720
NOELLE: We can talk
about it in the car, okay?

12:12.720 --> 12:14.690
RYAN: I want chili!
- That's my fault.

12:14.690 --> 12:16.510
I put chili in his head.

12:16.510 --> 12:19.060
So why don't you both
join me for dinner?

12:19.060 --> 12:20.790
Oh, no, we couldn't.
I... Thank you.

12:20.790 --> 12:23.860
Nonsense. I've made
enough for an army.

12:23.860 --> 12:26.080
Growing boys need
more than burgers,

12:26.080 --> 12:27.970
don't you think?

12:29.060 --> 12:30.800
Yeah.

12:30.800 --> 12:32.240
Sure.
Thank you.

12:32.240 --> 12:33.690
Ah.
Wonderful!

12:33.690 --> 12:34.880
Please say
"thank you." Yeah?

12:34.880 --> 12:37.050
- Thank you.
- Good boy.

12:37.050 --> 12:38.650
- Good night, Principal Jim.
- Good night, Ryan.

12:38.650 --> 12:39.880
- Thank you.
- I'll see you in a minute.

12:39.880 --> 12:40.890
- Enjoy the chili.
- I'll see you. Thank you.

12:40.890 --> 12:41.990
Come here, buddy.

12:41.990 --> 12:43.000
[WHISPERS] Hey!

12:43.000 --> 12:44.870
I'll see you later.

12:44.870 --> 12:46.240
Have a good night.

12:46.240 --> 12:47.660
Yeah.
You too.

12:47.660 --> 12:48.680
JIM: Good job.

12:48.680 --> 12:50.300
Thank you.

12:54.920 --> 12:56.250
NOELLE: They just look at you

12:56.250 --> 12:58.060
and make assumptions, you know?

12:58.060 --> 12:59.860
- LYDIA: Mmm.
- NOELLE: Like,

12:59.860 --> 13:01.660
I'm dressing for tips, asshole.

13:01.660 --> 13:04.440
I don't actually like you.

13:04.440 --> 13:06.260
I'm sorry.
I, um...

13:06.260 --> 13:10.030
I try not to swear around Ryan.

13:10.030 --> 13:11.460
I've never heard him

13:11.460 --> 13:15.010
use language like that.

13:15.010 --> 13:17.190
Anyway, it's just like,

13:17.190 --> 13:18.960
just because I bring you a drink

13:18.960 --> 13:20.200
doesn't mean that
you have a right

13:20.200 --> 13:21.660
to grab my rear, right?

13:21.660 --> 13:23.230
LYDIA: Right!
[NOELLE CHUCKLES]

13:23.230 --> 13:24.530
What did you do?

13:24.530 --> 13:26.760
I dumped that Long Island
Iced Tea right in his lap.

13:26.760 --> 13:28.450
[CHUCKLES]

13:28.450 --> 13:29.970
It's actually why I was late.

13:29.970 --> 13:31.670
I kind of got chewed
out by my manager

13:31.670 --> 13:32.970
after my shift.

13:32.970 --> 13:35.510
Maybe you should get
a different job.

13:35.510 --> 13:37.040
One where you're not
around so many...

13:37.040 --> 13:38.260
Assholes?

13:38.260 --> 13:39.700
I was going to say "men."

13:39.700 --> 13:41.250
NOELLE: Oh. Right.

13:41.250 --> 13:43.150
Mmm.

13:43.150 --> 13:45.050
Do you have a boyfriend?

13:45.050 --> 13:46.650
Or girlfriend?

13:46.650 --> 13:48.050
Whatever.

13:49.050 --> 13:50.650
I was married.

13:50.650 --> 13:53.540
Uh, he was a mistake.

13:55.270 --> 13:56.330
RYAN: Ms. Clements.

13:56.330 --> 13:58.360
Am I Thomas Edison?

14:00.230 --> 14:01.440
You are.

14:01.440 --> 14:03.030
Well done.

14:03.030 --> 14:04.400
[CHUCKLES]

14:04.400 --> 14:05.860
We were playing
Twenty Questions.

14:05.860 --> 14:07.440
He is so special.

14:07.440 --> 14:09.260
You're very blessed.

14:09.260 --> 14:10.800
NOELLE: I know.

14:10.800 --> 14:12.680
He deserves more.

14:12.680 --> 14:14.890
Better.
I don't know.

14:14.890 --> 14:16.860
But all he has is me.

14:16.860 --> 14:19.280
So...

14:19.280 --> 14:20.320
You could be better.

14:20.320 --> 14:21.350
[DARK MUSIC]

14:21.350 --> 14:22.760
NOELLE: Hmm.

14:22.760 --> 14:23.760
[PENCIL SCRATCHING LOUDLY]

14:23.760 --> 14:24.790
[FLOORBOARDS CREAKING]

14:57.390 --> 14:59.390
[DOOR OPENS, CLOSES]

15:11.670 --> 15:12.880
Bless you for sharing

15:12.880 --> 15:14.680
what you knew

15:14.680 --> 15:16.690
about Ofmatthew.

15:18.140 --> 15:20.810
No telling where that
might have gone.

15:22.650 --> 15:24.680
You're welcome, Aunt Lydia.

15:34.490 --> 15:35.930
[DOOR OPENS]

15:35.930 --> 15:37.130
[SIGHS]

15:38.130 --> 15:39.230
[DOOR CLOSES]

15:41.240 --> 15:42.780
LAWRENCE: Back so soon?

15:43.860 --> 15:45.340
It wasn't time.

15:45.340 --> 15:46.970
LAWRENCE: Oh.

15:48.610 --> 15:50.030
[LAWRENCE SIGHS]

15:53.260 --> 15:55.160
Commander Lawrence, sir.

15:55.960 --> 15:57.030
I need to know if you've learned

15:57.030 --> 15:58.880
anything about Hannah
or the Mackenzies

15:58.880 --> 16:00.900
- and where they...
- LAWRENCE: No.

16:02.490 --> 16:04.520
Don't ask me again.

16:08.660 --> 16:10.660
I don't know where she is.

16:12.460 --> 16:14.690
And I don't know
anybody who does.

16:16.000 --> 16:18.070
Go to your room.

16:22.030 --> 16:24.010
[OMINOUS MUSIC]

16:49.870 --> 16:52.570
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

17:12.260 --> 17:14.089
[DRAGGING FINGER ACROSS CARPET]

17:21.630 --> 17:23.270
JUNE: <i>Who can remember pain,</i>

17:23.270 --> 17:25.270
<i>once it's over?</i>

17:25.270 --> 17:26.500
<i>All that remains of it</i>

17:26.500 --> 17:27.869
<i>is a shadow.</i>

17:27.869 --> 17:29.470
<i>Not in the mind even,</i>

17:29.470 --> 17:31.580
<i>in the flesh.</i>

17:31.580 --> 17:33.610
<i>Pain marks you,</i>

17:33.610 --> 17:35.830
<i>but too deep to see.</i>

17:35.830 --> 17:37.870
<i>Out of sight, out of mind.</i>

17:37.870 --> 17:39.780
[KNOCKING]
[DOOR OPENS]

17:40.760 --> 17:41.790
You're awake.

17:42.750 --> 17:43.770
What is it?

17:43.770 --> 17:45.610
They said to get dressed.

17:45.610 --> 17:47.640
Birthmobile's
waiting downstairs.

18:02.490 --> 18:04.510
[SPIRITUAL INSTRUMENTAL MUSIC]
[CHOIR VOCALIZING]

18:04.510 --> 18:05.540
HANDMAIDS: [CHANTING] Breathe.

18:05.540 --> 18:06.570
AUNT LYDIA: That's it.

18:06.570 --> 18:08.150
Breathe through it, Ofandy.

18:08.150 --> 18:10.050
[OFANDY WAILING]

18:11.220 --> 18:13.240
JUNE: <i>How did that rhyme go?</i>

18:13.240 --> 18:15.660
<i>The one we'd jump rope to?</i>

18:15.660 --> 18:16.780
<i>Tinker, tailor,</i>

18:16.780 --> 18:18.160
<i>soldier, sailor,</i>

18:18.160 --> 18:19.670
<i>rich man, poor man,</i>

18:19.670 --> 18:20.850
<i>beggar man, thief.</i>

18:20.850 --> 18:22.450
<i>A game to tell</i>

18:22.450 --> 18:23.920
<i>what our children
would grow up to be.</i>

18:23.920 --> 18:25.810
HANDMAIDS: [CHANTING] Push.

18:25.810 --> 18:28.060
JUNE: <i>The list is a lot shorter now.</i>

18:28.060 --> 18:29.870
<i>Especially if it's a girl.</i>

18:29.870 --> 18:31.230
<i>Martha, Jezebel,</i>

18:31.230 --> 18:32.480
<i>Handmaid, Wife.</i>

18:32.480 --> 18:33.720
[OFANDY GASPING]

18:33.720 --> 18:35.380
HANDMAIDS: [CHANTING] Push.

18:35.380 --> 18:36.670
AUNT LYDIA: All right.
How are we doing?

18:36.670 --> 18:37.700
AUNT ELIZABETH: I see the head!

18:37.700 --> 18:38.890
We see the head!
[OFANDY SCREAMING]

18:38.890 --> 18:40.930
HANDMAIDS: [CHANTING] Breathe.

18:40.930 --> 18:43.050
AUNT LYDIA: Push. Push.
HANDMAIDS: [CHANTING] Push.

18:43.050 --> 18:45.040
AUNT LYDIA: Breathe!
HANDMAIDS: [CHANTING] Push.

18:45.040 --> 18:46.820
[OFANDY CONTINUES SCREAMING]

18:50.270 --> 18:52.100
[MUFFLED SCREAMING]

18:54.250 --> 18:55.290
WIFE: Oh, here she is!

18:55.290 --> 18:56.290
[WIFE GASPS]

18:56.290 --> 18:57.770
AUNT LYDIA: You did it, love.

18:57.770 --> 18:59.450
Good girl!
She's beautiful!

18:59.450 --> 19:00.810
[ALL CHATTERING JOYFULLY]

19:00.810 --> 19:03.070
AUNT LYDIA: There we are.

19:03.070 --> 19:04.730
[CHATTERING STOPS]

19:10.860 --> 19:12.780
[GASPS]

19:28.360 --> 19:31.210
No.

19:31.210 --> 19:33.280
No.

19:33.280 --> 19:34.870
[CRYING] No!
It can't be!

19:34.870 --> 19:36.860
No!
No!

19:36.860 --> 19:37.880
It's my daughter!

19:37.880 --> 19:40.580
WIFE 2: Come!
Come, come!

19:40.580 --> 19:42.210
She's sleeping!

19:42.210 --> 19:43.590
[SOBBING]

19:57.480 --> 19:58.500
AUNT LYDIA: No, no.

19:58.500 --> 19:59.500
You shouldn't be seeing this.

19:59.500 --> 20:01.250
Come along.
Get some air.

20:01.250 --> 20:03.260
[SOBBING]

20:19.450 --> 20:21.470
[SOMBER PIANO MUSIC]

20:32.790 --> 20:34.810
AUNT ELIZABETH: Go to your sister.

20:54.010 --> 20:55.440
JUNE: <i>I didn't know</i>

20:55.440 --> 20:56.870
<i>what it was that I felt,</i>

20:56.870 --> 20:57.890
<i>there with Ofandy</i>

20:57.890 --> 21:00.030
<i>and her baby.</i>

21:00.030 --> 21:02.240
<i>But I do now.</i>

21:02.240 --> 21:03.490
<i>Relief.</i>
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

21:03.490 --> 21:04.580
[DOOR OPENS]

21:07.660 --> 21:09.890
[LAWRENCE SIGHS]

21:09.890 --> 21:11.510
So.

21:14.230 --> 21:16.250
A boy or a girl?

21:16.250 --> 21:19.880
Mrs. Lawrence will want to know.

21:19.880 --> 21:21.470
OFJOSEPH: Dead.

21:21.470 --> 21:22.930
Oh.

21:25.260 --> 21:27.010
Well.

21:27.010 --> 21:29.040
She... she doesn't
have to know that

21:29.040 --> 21:31.180
when you tell her.

21:31.180 --> 21:32.450
Maybe you could

21:32.450 --> 21:34.130
spend some time
with her tomorrow.

21:34.130 --> 21:35.400
Playing cards or...

21:35.400 --> 21:36.670
something.

21:36.670 --> 21:38.630
You're...

21:38.630 --> 21:39.650
you're good with her.

21:39.650 --> 21:41.660
You're good <i>for</i> her.

21:44.050 --> 21:45.650
Anyway.

21:45.650 --> 21:46.890
You act like you care

21:46.890 --> 21:48.730
about your wife.

21:50.000 --> 21:52.600
I mean, I...

21:52.600 --> 21:54.040
I know you don't
give a shit about

21:54.040 --> 21:55.900
the rest of us.

21:57.040 --> 21:58.060
But you do realize

21:58.060 --> 22:00.250
that this world
that you built...

22:00.250 --> 22:01.570
here,

22:01.570 --> 22:03.590
is destroying her.

22:05.250 --> 22:06.670
And that,

22:06.670 --> 22:09.300
with <i>one</i> phone call,

22:11.720 --> 22:13.730
you could have her out.

22:15.440 --> 22:18.100
But you're keeping her hostage.

22:23.800 --> 22:25.820
You're not protecting her.

22:27.340 --> 22:29.380
You're killing her.

22:42.680 --> 22:44.720
I'll bet that felt good.

22:53.400 --> 22:54.820
[DOOR CLOSES]

23:02.870 --> 23:04.310
[LAUGHS]

23:09.650 --> 23:11.560
The Carvers.

23:12.750 --> 23:14.650
I know it's been
a trying day, ladies,

23:14.650 --> 23:17.920
but God sees our labors.

23:17.920 --> 23:20.790
The Carvers are quick to anger.

23:20.790 --> 23:22.050
They need someone quiet.

23:22.050 --> 23:23.400
Calm.

23:24.920 --> 23:26.140
Sonya.

23:26.140 --> 23:27.140
AUNT LYDIA: Ah.

23:27.140 --> 23:29.450
They don't want a
Handmaid of color.

23:30.730 --> 23:31.980
[SIGHS]

23:33.240 --> 23:34.250
Vivian?

23:36.680 --> 23:39.370
AUNT LYDIA: Oh. Very good.

23:39.370 --> 23:41.110
[DOGS BARKING OUTSIDE]

23:41.110 --> 23:42.880
Sonya would be good

23:42.880 --> 23:44.150
for the Holbecks.

23:44.150 --> 23:45.250
Where'd I put them?

23:45.250 --> 23:46.880
They're right here.

23:46.880 --> 23:48.260
AUNT LYDIA: Oh.

23:48.260 --> 23:50.270
Thank you.

23:51.890 --> 23:53.050
AUNT ELIZABETH: There is [SIGHS]

23:53.050 --> 23:55.460
the question of Ofandy.

23:55.460 --> 23:56.670
Once she's ready to return

23:56.670 --> 23:57.860
to service, of course.

23:57.860 --> 23:59.260
The Allstons won't have her back.

23:59.260 --> 24:00.890
They already told me.

24:00.890 --> 24:01.910
And word will have gotten around

24:01.910 --> 24:02.940
about her failure today.

24:02.940 --> 24:04.460
Poor thing.

24:04.460 --> 24:05.650
I know.

24:05.650 --> 24:08.010
Such a good girl.

24:08.010 --> 24:10.110
Unlike some.

24:10.110 --> 24:11.480
Why our Lord above

24:11.480 --> 24:12.860
would withhold His blessings

24:12.860 --> 24:14.480
from a girl like that

24:14.480 --> 24:16.460
and give <i>two</i> healthy babies

24:16.460 --> 24:19.400
to someone like Ofjoseph.

24:20.470 --> 24:22.250
I have tried with that one,

24:22.250 --> 24:24.040
so help me.

24:24.040 --> 24:26.260
Sometimes there's just a bad apple.

24:26.260 --> 24:27.930
Hmph. Amen.

24:27.930 --> 24:28.960
AUNTS: Amen.

24:30.460 --> 24:31.620
[CHRISTMAS MUSIC
PLAYING ON RADIO]

24:31.620 --> 24:32.650
LYDIA: One more.

24:32.650 --> 24:34.650
NOELLE: Oh, no, Lydia.
It's too many.

24:34.650 --> 24:36.450
LYDIA: Here, honey.
- Is it an iPad?

24:36.450 --> 24:38.210
[LYDIA LAUGHS]

24:38.210 --> 24:39.230
LYDIA: Honey.

24:39.230 --> 24:41.270
It's what we had before iPads.

24:41.270 --> 24:42.680
[CHUCKLES]
I know,

24:42.680 --> 24:44.180
how did we ever survive?

24:46.360 --> 24:47.670
NOELLE: Buddy!

24:47.670 --> 24:49.710
Give her a hug.

24:51.010 --> 24:52.220
What do you say?

24:52.220 --> 24:53.390
Thank you, Aunt Lydia.

24:53.390 --> 24:55.650
NOELLE: Uh-huh. And?
- You're welcome, dear.

24:55.650 --> 24:57.820
RYAN: And we've got
something for you, too.

24:57.820 --> 25:00.020
Oh. You shouldn't
have done that.

25:00.020 --> 25:01.660
Please.

25:02.610 --> 25:03.870
[RYAN GRUNTS]

25:03.870 --> 25:05.680
[LYDIA LAUGHS]

25:05.680 --> 25:08.450
Aww. Thank you.

25:08.450 --> 25:10.470
You're welcome.

25:19.250 --> 25:20.450
LYDIA: Oh!

25:20.450 --> 25:22.660
[CHUCKLING]
One of the reasons

25:22.660 --> 25:23.800
I like working with children

25:23.800 --> 25:24.870
is that I don't have to bother

25:24.870 --> 25:25.890
with this nonsense.

25:25.890 --> 25:27.250
Well, it'll get you out there.

25:27.250 --> 25:29.430
You can't be alone.

25:29.430 --> 25:31.460
I'm not alone.

25:33.060 --> 25:34.930
I know.

25:34.930 --> 25:36.760
I just mean, um...

25:36.760 --> 25:37.870
it doesn't seem like

25:37.870 --> 25:39.050
there's been someone special

25:39.050 --> 25:40.160
for you in a while,

25:40.160 --> 25:41.830
and you deserve that.

25:41.830 --> 25:43.700
Because you have
so much love to give.

25:43.700 --> 25:45.360
Oh!

25:47.260 --> 25:48.580
You should save your money.

25:48.580 --> 25:49.600
NOELLE: Employee discount.

25:49.600 --> 25:51.870
<i>And</i> I picked out every color

25:51.870 --> 25:53.060
special for you.

25:53.060 --> 25:54.360
LYDIA: Oh.

25:54.360 --> 25:55.400
Can I?

25:57.710 --> 25:59.660
Oh, all right.
[NOELLE LAUGHS]

26:01.690 --> 26:03.470
Okay.

26:03.470 --> 26:05.690
Now, I love this foundation.

26:05.690 --> 26:06.690
Mmm.

26:06.690 --> 26:08.310
'Cause you don't need a lot

26:08.310 --> 26:10.330
to get <i>really</i> good coverage.

26:11.870 --> 26:13.730
[NOELLE GIGGLES]

26:13.730 --> 26:14.970
Okay.

26:17.300 --> 26:18.470
[NOELLE CHUCKLES]

26:23.610 --> 26:24.740
How is Jason?

26:24.740 --> 26:26.030
That dirtbag?

26:26.030 --> 26:27.680
Kicked him to the curb.

26:27.680 --> 26:28.680
Good.

26:28.680 --> 26:29.690
Okay.
Blush.

26:29.690 --> 26:30.700
Mmm-hmm.

26:30.700 --> 26:33.330
Just goes on the apples
of your cheeks.

26:33.330 --> 26:34.990
Okay.

26:41.290 --> 26:42.930
I met someone, though.

26:42.930 --> 26:44.160
He's in IT.

26:44.160 --> 26:46.590
Oh! There's a lot
of good jobs in that field.

26:48.230 --> 26:49.600
Does he like kids?

26:49.600 --> 26:51.500
He's got two of his own, so...

26:51.500 --> 26:52.500
yeah.

26:52.500 --> 26:54.940
And he says
he's gonna leave his wife.

26:56.140 --> 26:57.860
I know I'm not as far along

26:57.860 --> 26:58.900
as we would like,

26:58.900 --> 27:01.550
but I'm trying.

27:01.550 --> 27:02.880
That's what counts, dear.

27:02.880 --> 27:04.620
NOELLE: Mmm-hmm. Okay.

27:04.620 --> 27:06.250
The eyes.

27:06.250 --> 27:07.530
- Okay.
- Mmm-hmm.

27:07.530 --> 27:10.590
This color is great
for a daytime look,

27:10.590 --> 27:13.560
and this one for a night out.

27:13.560 --> 27:15.060
A night out?
Yeah.

27:15.060 --> 27:17.700
Come on. We gotta
get you out there, Lydia.

27:20.530 --> 27:22.130
LYDIA: Hmm.

27:23.130 --> 27:24.330
[LYDIA CHUCKLES]

27:26.080 --> 27:28.320
If I'm going to try harder,

27:28.320 --> 27:29.740
so are you.

27:31.460 --> 27:32.470
Okay.

27:32.470 --> 27:34.230
NOELLE: Okay.

27:34.230 --> 27:36.240
[UPBEAT DANCE MUSIC]

27:36.240 --> 27:38.260
[INDISTINCT CHATTERING]

27:47.360 --> 27:49.020
Hi.

27:51.130 --> 27:52.670
WOMAN: May I check your coat?

27:52.670 --> 27:54.330
Oh yes, thank you.

27:56.240 --> 27:57.870
Thank you.

27:58.550 --> 27:59.590
Oh.

28:28.890 --> 28:30.900
Oh!
[CHUCKLES]

28:32.920 --> 28:34.700
Hi.

28:35.610 --> 28:36.640
Hi.

28:36.640 --> 28:37.890
- LYDIA: How are you?
- Good.

28:37.890 --> 28:39.640
LYDIA: Oh, my goodness.
I was about to leave.

28:39.640 --> 28:41.050
I thought I was maybe
in the wrong place.

28:41.050 --> 28:42.450
- Well, I'm glad you're here.
- LYDIA: Me too.

28:42.450 --> 28:43.960
- You look lovely.
- LYDIA: Thank you so much.

28:43.960 --> 28:45.650
[LYDIA CHUCKLES]
I see.

28:45.650 --> 28:47.040
JIM: This just seemed festive.

28:47.040 --> 28:48.770
Sure, sure.

28:48.770 --> 28:49.880
[SLOW GUITAR MUSIC]

28:49.880 --> 28:51.250
JIM: Last New Year's,

28:51.250 --> 28:52.820
I made mac and cheese...

28:52.820 --> 28:54.420
[LYDIA LAUGHS]

28:54.420 --> 28:56.240
...had a bottle of
sparkling cider.

28:56.240 --> 28:57.280
LYDIA: Oh, my.

28:57.280 --> 28:59.260
JIM: Fell asleep by 10:00.

28:59.260 --> 29:00.700
So, this is a big improvement.

29:00.700 --> 29:01.880
I should say.

29:01.880 --> 29:02.890
Oh, my.

29:02.890 --> 29:05.360
- Oh, no, thank you.
- JIM: Lydia.

29:05.360 --> 29:07.200
Special occasion.

29:08.890 --> 29:10.230
Excuse me.

29:12.780 --> 29:14.810
LYDIA: Thank you very much.

29:14.810 --> 29:16.450
JIM: Thanks.

29:17.980 --> 29:20.050
Thank you.

29:20.050 --> 29:22.410
Hard to believe teaching's
your second career.

29:22.410 --> 29:24.020
- Oh...
- JIM: You're a natural.

29:24.020 --> 29:26.690
Well,
family law was good practice.

29:26.690 --> 29:29.030
I mean, the system <i>now</i> is better

29:29.030 --> 29:30.760
because it's all
been privatized,

29:30.760 --> 29:33.050
but then it was
very frustrating.

29:33.050 --> 29:35.060
'Cause you couldn't
help as many children

29:35.060 --> 29:36.530
as you wanted to.
You know?

29:36.530 --> 29:39.740
I've never seen
anyone so devoted.

29:39.740 --> 29:41.780
I've always admired you.

29:47.660 --> 29:49.320
I'm fond of you, too.

29:52.030 --> 29:53.570
- Oh, my.
- JIM: Wow.

29:53.570 --> 29:55.440
LYDIA: It's a feast.
[JIM CHUCKLES]

29:55.440 --> 29:57.910
JIM: It looks great.
Thank you.

29:57.910 --> 30:00.580
LYDIA: Oh, my goodness.
JIM: Shall we say grace?

30:01.670 --> 30:02.790
Lord, we thank you

30:02.790 --> 30:04.030
for your many blessings.

30:04.030 --> 30:05.660
For this food, good fellowship,

30:05.660 --> 30:07.670
and the year
ahead. Amen.

30:07.670 --> 30:09.320
LYDIA: Amen.

30:11.030 --> 30:12.460
And cheers.

30:12.460 --> 30:13.480
LYDIA: Cheers.

30:17.590 --> 30:20.620
["ISLANDS IN THE STREAM" BY KENNY ROGERS FT.
DOLLY PARTON PLAYING ON KARAOKE MACHINE]

30:20.620 --> 30:22.180
[CROWD CHEERING]

30:22.180 --> 30:23.840
[EXCLAIMING HAPPILY]

30:26.680 --> 30:28.450
<i>♪ Baby,
when I met you ♪</i>

30:28.450 --> 30:31.450
<i>♪ There was peace unknown ♪</i>

30:31.450 --> 30:33.240
<i>♪ I set out to get you ♪</i>

30:33.240 --> 30:35.650
<i>♪ With a fine-tooth comb ♪</i>

30:35.650 --> 30:38.260
<i>♪ I was soft inside ♪</i>

30:38.260 --> 30:41.870
<i>♪ There was somethin' going on ♪</i>

30:41.870 --> 30:43.180
[LAUGHING]

30:43.180 --> 30:44.210
[CROWD CHEERING]

30:44.210 --> 30:45.460
I forgot this is a duet.

30:45.460 --> 30:46.500
I might need some help.

30:46.500 --> 30:47.680
<i>♪ Do something to me ♪</i>

30:47.680 --> 30:50.790
<i>♪ That I can't explain ♪</i>

30:50.790 --> 30:51.880
I need help.

30:51.880 --> 30:53.550
Oh, you over there!
Come over here!

30:53.550 --> 30:54.810
- Me? No!
- JIM: Yeah, you!

30:54.810 --> 30:56.170
- No, I can't!
- JIM: Miss! Please?

30:56.170 --> 30:57.170
Please!
Please!

30:57.170 --> 30:58.420
Come on!
Come on.

30:58.420 --> 30:59.640
Would you help me, please?

30:59.640 --> 31:00.670
Please!
Please!

31:00.670 --> 31:01.680
No way!

31:01.680 --> 31:03.450
No, Jim.
I don't sing!

31:03.450 --> 31:04.900
Come on.
It's a duet!

31:04.900 --> 31:05.930
It's a duet.

31:05.930 --> 31:07.060
Please, help me out.

31:07.060 --> 31:09.290
Come on, Lydia!
Come on!

31:09.290 --> 31:11.240
[CROWD CHEERING]

31:11.240 --> 31:13.280
Lydia Clements, everyone!

31:15.650 --> 31:16.660
LYDIA: Okay,
here we go.

31:16.660 --> 31:17.700
